#. Tag: title
#: sle_update_preparation.xml:64
#, no-c-format
msgid "New 4096-bit signing key for &sle; 15"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: sle_update_preparation.xml:65
#, no-c-format
msgid "Mid 2023, the &sle; 15 product family switched over from a RSA 2048-bit signing key to a new RSA 4096-bit key. This change covers RPM packages, package repositories and ISO signatures. Old repositories that are not updated anymore and RPMs released up to the switch-over date, will remain signed with the old 2048-bit key."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: sle_update_preparation.xml:71
#, no-c-format
msgid "If you update your system, the new key is automatically imported into the RPM keyring from the <package>suse-build-key</package> package on &slea; 15 SP 4 and SP5 as well as the LTSS versions of &slea; 15 SP1, SP2 and SP3."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: sle_update_preparation.xml:76
#, no-c-format
msgid "If the key has not been imported yet, you can manually import it with:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: sle_update_preparation.xml:79
#, no-c-format
msgid "&prompt.sudo;<command>rpm --import /usr/lib/rpm/gnupg/keys/gpg-pubkey-3fa1d6ce-63c9481c.asc</command>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: sle_update_preparation.xml:80
#, no-c-format
msgid "If you are running an older version of &slea; or did not import the new key, you will be asked to trust it during the upgrade. Make sure the fingerprint matches:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: sle_update_preparation.xml:84
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"pub   rsa4096/0xF74F09BC3FA1D6CE 2023-01-19 [SC] [expires: 2027-01-18]\n"
"Key fingerprint = 7F00 9157 B127 B994 D5CF  BE76 F74F 09BC 3FA1 D6CE\n"
"uid           SUSE Package Signing Key &lt;build@suse.de&gt;"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: sle_update_preparation.xml:87
#, no-c-format
msgid "Additionally, a reserve 4096-bit RSA key for disaster recovery purposes was imported:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: sle_update_preparation.xml:90
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"pub   rsa4096/0xA1BFC02BD588DC46 2023-01-19 [SC] [expires: 2033-01-16]\n"
"Key fingerprint = B56E 5601 41D8 F654 2DFF  3BF9 A1BF C02B D588 DC46\n"
"uid           SUSE Package Signing Key (reserve key) &lt;build@suse.de&gt;"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: sle_update_preparation.xml:93
#, no-c-format
msgid "This key can be manually imported using:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: sle_update_preparation.xml:96
#, no-c-format
msgid "&prompt.sudo;<command>rpm --import /usr/lib/rpm/gnupg/keys/gpg-pubkey-d588dc46-63c939db.asc</command>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: sle_update_preparation.xml:97
#, no-c-format
msgid "Both keys can also be found on the installation media and the &suse; website at <link xlink:href=\"https://www.suse.com/support/security/keys/\"/> ."
